g.text: Percentile: A point in a distribution below which a specified percentage of the values fall.
Can be conceptualized as 'area under the curve' calculated from left to right. The 100th percentile the entire area.
z-score: Distance from the mean (µ) in standard deviations (σ). Note: each segment of the distribution represents 0.5 standard deviations.
Quantile: A location on the distributions x-axis. The z-score is a type of quantile. When you have a µ = 0 and a σ = 1, the x-axis is z-scores.
